Q. What are combinators? give examples of how you can use them?
ans- It explains the relationship between the selector.
    There are four different combinators-
    - descendant selector (space)
    -child selector (>)
    -adjacent sibling selector (+)
    -general sibling(~)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What does object-fit do?
ans-  object-fit property is used to specify how an image or video should be resized
        syntax-
                object-fit : fill | contain | cover | none

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What does rotate do?
ans- The rotate CSS property allows you to specify rotation transforms individually and 
    independently of the transform property.


    -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What rule can be used to define animations?
ans- animations lets an element gradually change from one style to another.
    you can change the as many css propery you want as many times you want.
    To use animation, you must first specify some keyframes for the animation.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.When working with attribute selectors, how can you select elements which contain a particular attribute value?
ans-  The attribute selector is used to select element with a specified attribute.
        ex-input[type="button"] {
            width: 120px;
            margin-left: 35px;
            display: block;
                }

------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What does @media do?
ans- @media is used in media query to apply different style for different
        devices It is used to make pages responsive.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What can be used to override properties of an element?
ans- To override property of an element we can write !important .






----------------------------------------------------------
Q. how can we apply same styles to multiple selectors?
ans- we can apply same style to mulitple selector by grouping them.
        example- div, p { color: red; }